HEADWORD: Epicleidium
<hw>Ep`i*clei"di*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>'epi`</grk> upon + <?/ a little key.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>A projection, formed by a separate ossification, at the scapular
end of the clavicle of many birds.</def>⟦br⟧
